# API Routes Must Use force-dynamic

Every API route file (`src/app/api/**/route.ts`) MUST include this export at the top level:

```typescript
export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";
```

## Why

Next.js Data Cache can serve stale responses from API routes. This directive ensures every route is dynamically rendered at request time.

## Before Pushing to GitHub

1. Verify ALL API route files contain `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"`
2. Any NEW API route must include it before the first `export function`
3. Never remove this line from existing routes

## Example

```typescript
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from "next/server";
import { getServerSession } from "next-auth";
import { authOptions } from "@/lib/auth";

export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  // ...
}
```
